<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Morphological identification.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="109">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yu J. Wang &amp; J. Chen, PloS ONE 13 (7): e 0199416 (12" authorityYear="2018" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Saussurea" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Saussurea bogedaensis" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bogedaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">Saussurea bogedaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurea bogedaensis in Buduun Khargait river, Baitag Bogd Mt, Uyench sum, Khovd Province, Mongolia. A general habit in Baitag Bogd Mt, DzG region B fruiting C leaves D pappus E phyllaries. Photos: 28 July 2019, Sh. Baasanmunkh." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.160.55603.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450534" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">1</figureCitation>
) was recently discovered on Bogeda Mt in Xinjiang, China by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0199416" author="Chen, J" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" refId="B4" refString="Chen, J, Wang, Y-J, 2018. New Saussurea (Asteraceae) species from Bogeda Mountain, eastern Tianshan, China, and inference of its evolutionary history and medical usage. PLoS One 13(7): e0199416. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0199416" title="New Saussurea (Asteraceae) species from Bogeda Mountain, eastern Tianshan, China, and inference of its evolutionary history and medical usage. PLoS One 13 (7): e 0199416." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0199416" year="2018">Chen and Wang (2018)</bibRefCitation>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Distribution of S. bogedaensis (red dots), S. involucrata (blue dots) and S. orgaadayi (green dots) in Mongolia, Russia and Chinese Tien-Shan Mts based on field surveys and herbarium materials as well as specimens from China based on the publications of Chen and Wang (2018) and Chen et al. (2019). Region numbers on the Mongolian map are phytogeographical regions according to Grubov (1982): 6 - Khovd, 7 - Mongolian Altai, 10 - Depression of Great Lakes and 14 - Dzungarian Gobi." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.160.55603.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450536" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">3</figureCitation>
). This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. involucrata" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="involucrata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">S. involucrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. orgaadayi" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="orgaadayi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">S. orgaadayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Saussurea orgaadayi in Khukh Nuur, Munkhkhairkhan sum, Khovd Province, Mongolia A general habit in Munkhkhairkhan Mt, MA region B fruiting C flowering D pappus E phyllaries. Photos: 29 July 2016, B. Oyuntsetseg (A, C) Sh. Baasanmunkh (B, D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.160.55603.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450535" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">2</figureCitation>
), but several morphological characteristics of the bracts, involucres and phyllaries differentiate them (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0199416" author="Chen, J" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" refId="B4" refString="Chen, J, Wang, Y-J, 2018. New Saussurea (Asteraceae) species from Bogeda Mountain, eastern Tianshan, China, and inference of its evolutionary history and medical usage. PLoS One 13(7): e0199416. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0199416" title="New Saussurea (Asteraceae) species from Bogeda Mountain, eastern Tianshan, China, and inference of its evolutionary history and medical usage. PLoS One 13 (7): e 0199416." url="https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0199416" year="2018">Chen and Wang 2018</bibRefCitation>
). In particular, 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. bogedaensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="bogedaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">S. bogedaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by having elliptic, apically obtuse stem leaves (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurea bogedaensis in Buduun Khargait river, Baitag Bogd Mt, Uyench sum, Khovd Province, Mongolia. A general habit in Baitag Bogd Mt, DzG region B fruiting C leaves D pappus E phyllaries. Photos: 28 July 2019, Sh. Baasanmunkh." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.160.55603.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450534" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">1C</figureCitation>
) vs. lanceolate, long-acuminate stem leaves in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. orgaadayi" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="orgaadayi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">S. orgaadayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Saussurea orgaadayi in Khukh Nuur, Munkhkhairkhan sum, Khovd Province, Mongolia A general habit in Munkhkhairkhan Mt, MA region B fruiting C flowering D pappus E phyllaries. Photos: 29 July 2016, B. Oyuntsetseg (A, C) Sh. Baasanmunkh (B, D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.160.55603.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450535" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">2A</figureCitation>
); dirty white pappus colour (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurea bogedaensis in Buduun Khargait river, Baitag Bogd Mt, Uyench sum, Khovd Province, Mongolia. A general habit in Baitag Bogd Mt, DzG region B fruiting C leaves D pappus E phyllaries. Photos: 28 July 2019, Sh. Baasanmunkh." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.160.55603.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450534" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">1D</figureCitation>
) vs. straw-coloured pappi in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. orgaadayi" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="orgaadayi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">S. orgaadayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Saussurea orgaadayi in Khukh Nuur, Munkhkhairkhan sum, Khovd Province, Mongolia A general habit in Munkhkhairkhan Mt, MA region B fruiting C flowering D pappus E phyllaries. Photos: 29 July 2016, B. Oyuntsetseg (A, C) Sh. Baasanmunkh (B, D, E)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.160.55603.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450535" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">2D</figureCitation>
); densely pubescent phyllaries (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Saussurea bogedaensis in Buduun Khargait river, Baitag Bogd Mt, Uyench sum, Khovd Province, Mongolia. A general habit in Baitag Bogd Mt, DzG region B fruiting C leaves D pappus E phyllaries. Photos: 28 July 2019, Sh. Baasanmunkh." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.160.55603.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450534" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">1E</figureCitation>
) vs. glabrous phyllaries in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. involucrata" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="involucrata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">S. involucrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; and campanulate involucres in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. bogedaensis" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="bogedaensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">S. bogedaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. hemispherical involucres in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. involucrata" pageId="0" pageNumber="109" rank="species" species="involucrata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="109">S. involucrata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
